UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2604
1 A RESOLUTION adjourning the Senate in celebration, honor, and appreciation of
2 the Grayson County Historical Society on the occasion of its 50th anniversary.
3 WHEREAS, the Grayson County Historical Society was established in Leitchfield,
4 Kentucky, on August 30, 1976; and
5 WHEREAS, the Grayson County Historical Society is headquartered in the historic
6 Jack Thomas House, the oldest brick home in Grayson County, built around 1815 by the
7 first county court clerk, Jack Thomas; and
8 WHEREAS, in addition to the Jack Thomas House, the Grayson County Historical
9 Society owns and maintains a cemetery, log cabin, and two one-room schoolhouses,
10 which are routinely visited by local schoolchildren on field trips; and
11 WHEREAS, the mission of the Grayson County Historical Society is to work to
12 preserve the history of Grayson County and its families by accumulating relative
13 documents and other artifacts; and
14 WHEREAS, the Grayson County Historical Society hosts a comprehensive research
15 library and museum in the Jack Thomas House that is open weekdays to the public; and
16 WHEREAS, the Grayson County Historical Society has authored and published
17 numerous books and other materials of local historical interest; and
18 WHEREAS, the Grayson County Historical Society regularly hosts public meetings
19 featuring guest speakers on topics of local historical interest, open houses, presentations
20 to civic groups, fields trips to local historical sites, and other educational events and
21 opportunities; and
22 WHEREAS, the Grayson County Historical Society routinely publishes newsletters
23 for its membership which stretches across the United States and beyond; and
24 WHEREAS, the Grayson County Historical Society annually awards a scholarship
25 to a deserving Grayson County High School senior and sponsors the Junior Historical
26 Society at the high school; and
27 WHEREAS, the current board of directors of the Grayson County Historical
