1 Society includes President Scotty Gore, Vice President Melinda Baum, Secretary Rose
2 Booth, Treasurer Kelly Stevenson, and directors Bill Clemons, Shannon Harp, and
3 Allison Helm; and
4 WHEREAS, Mary Decker serves as Hostess and Librarian at the Jack Thomas
5 House; and
6 WHEREAS, the Grayson County Historical Society will celebrate its 50th
7 anniversary celebration at the Jack Thomas House in Leitchfield on Saturday, June 20,
8 2026, as part of a special event recognizing the 250th anniversary of the signing of the
9 United States of America's Declaration of Independence;
10 NOW, THEREFORE,
11 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
12 Kentucky:
13 Section 1. The Senate hereby extends its hearty congratulations to the Grayson
14 County Historical Society upon its 50th anniversary of service to the local community
15 and expresses its appreciation for the society's efforts to preserve and protect the history
16 of Grayson County.
17 Section 2. When the Senate adjourns this day, it does so in celebration, honor,
18 and appreciation of the Grayson County Historical Society.
19 Section 3. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
20 Resolution to Senator Stephen Meredith for delivery.
